    "A simple character-level reversal would detach niqqud (vowel marks) from their letters, since niqqud are combining Unicode characters that attach to the preceding letter. Aleph Tools reverses text in groups — each letter with its attached diacritics stays together — so vocalized text reverses correctly." : {
      "comment" : "Description of the text reversal feature, explaining how it reverses Hebrew text while keeping diacritics attached.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
