    "Adobe apps can support Hebrew natively, but the Middle Eastern text engine isn’t installed by default. To enable it:\n\n1. Open the Creative Cloud desktop app\n2. Go to Preferences › Apps\n3. Under the “Installing” section, change the language/text engine to “Tomech Ivrit” (Hebrew support)\n4. Uninstall the Adobe apps you use (After Effects, Premiere Pro, Photoshop, Illustrator, etc.)\n5. Reinstall them from Creative Cloud\n\nThe reinstalled apps will include the Middle Eastern text engine by default, giving you proper RTL text, correct character joining, and bidirectional support without needing to pre-reverse text." : {
      "comment" : "Text describing the steps to enable Hebrew support in Adobe apps using Tomech Ivrit.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "After reversal" : {
      "comment" : "A description of the app's RTL support.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
