      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Discovered in 1880 in Hezekiah’s Tunnel in Jerusalem, the Siloam Inscription (circa 701 BCE) describes the moment two teams of tunnelers met underground. It is one of the oldest known Hebrew inscriptions and is written entirely in Paleo-Hebrew. The original is in the Istanbul Archaeology Museum." : {
      "comment" : "Text describing the Siloam Inscription, including its historical context and the museum where the original is housed.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
