    "Niqqud (Vowel Points)" : {
      "comment" : "Title of a Hebrew lesson that explains how Hebrew marks vowels.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
    "Niqqud is a system of diacritical marks (dots and dashes) placed above or below Hebrew letters to indicate vowel sounds. Since the Hebrew alphabet only represents consonants, niqqud fills in the vowels that readers must otherwise infer from context." : {
      "comment" : "Explanation of niqqud, a system of diacritical marks used in Hebrew to indicate vowel sounds.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
